{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"baa7c2d3-1045-4723-8a04-8f82d26abf6b","content":"The working directory is empty and this isn't a git repository, so there are no local template definitions to inspect. However, I can give you the comparison based on the standard .NET `webapi` and `webapp` templates (from `dotnet new`):\n\n## `webapi` vs `webapp` — Parameter Comparison\n\n| Feature | `webapi` | `webapp` |\n|---------|----------|----------|\n| **Authentication** | ✅ `--auth` (None, Individual, IndividualB2C, SingleOrg, Windows) | ✅ `--auth` (same options) |\n| **AOT (Native AOT)** | ✅ `--aot` | ❌ Not supported |\n| **Framework** | `--framework` | `--framework` |\n| **Use controllers** | `--use-controllers` | N/A |\n| **Minimal APIs** | Default (yes) | N/A (uses Razor Pages) |\n| **HTTPS** | `--no-https` | `--no-https` |\n| **OpenAPI** | `--no-openapi` | N/A |\n| **Use Program.Main** | `--use-program-main` | `--use-program-main` |\n\n### Summary\n\n- **Authentication**: Both support `--auth` with the same options.\n- **AOT**: Only `webapi` supports `--aot` (Native AOT publishing). `webapp` relies on Razor Pages runtime compilation, which is incompatible with AOT.\n\nYou can verify on your machine with:\n```\ndotnet new webapi --help\ndotnet new webapp --help\n```\n\nWould you like me to scaffold one of these templates for you?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"627e76ae-ac4e-4c7e-889e-4753564bac45","outputTokens":392,"requestId":"4FC1:23ADA7:309E463:3531022:69FBE25A"},"id":"cebb0e4f-1d99-49b8-98ea-a2b837f60620","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:52:58.831Z","parentId":"1f58a598-dc4e-4f63-b52f-2b24c29eadb3"}
